snippet.textDisplay: If I would pick my favorite soda I would honestly pick a more regional variant, We have a soda in Sweden called Champis. Which is an odd one, the branding and bottle tries to mimic champagne. But it doesn't taste like champagne, It has hints of apple and grape. I don't know if it's true but I feel like it's mostly old people that like it, my dad and granddad liked it. We also have one called pommac which gets it's name from a cognac, this one tastes similar to Champis but it's less sweet. If i had to compare it to any american soda I would probably say a rootbeer or something. It's a unique flavor according to me. We also have seasonal sodas, Both for Christmas and Easter. I am declaring that Julmust and Påskmust are the same thing they just change the labels. Some people swear by that one is better than the other and that they are different. The flavor is a deep, dark flavor of almost beer but also spices that feel like Christmas. Think beer without the alcohol mixed with Coke. It's also crazy carbonated, they had to make the one that comes in the metal cans less fizzy cause the can couldn't hold it all in.  TL:DR I'm weird.

snippet.textDisplay:
How to play Heads Up 7-Up:
in a classroom
Choose 7 people to be "Up".
The rest of the class will follow same motion seen displayed by Eugene.
The "Up" people will touch the thumb of the person they choose and wait at the front of the classroom.
When all people have returned to the front, say "Heads Up 7-Up".
The "7-Up" at their desk will guess who choose their thumb- if you guess right you'll replace that person who chose you.
Repeat process till released for lunch.
Enjoy 😁😁😁😁

snippet.textDisplay: I was so prepared to suit up in chainmail armor and defend Dr. Pepper to the death, but then he put it in third place and I was... oh, okay... that's acceptable? But it made me think- why do I like Dr. Pepper so much? Where did this strange fixation with a specific soda brand begin? And as I lay on my floor pondering- it hit me! It all goes back to Freshman year, when little baby me downloaded Mystic Messenger and, in the kind of attempt to impersonate a fictional character that only a confused high schooler without a stable grasp on their personality could pull off, I drank unseemly amounts of Dr.Pepper in order to further align myself with saeyoung choi- or as many know him- 707.  This discovery led to the realization that most of my personality is traits stolen from fictional characters and internet personalities whom I admire! And if I am now forced to live within the confines of a mind who's come to realize this- so must many of you.
